---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Serbia Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/serbia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Montenegro for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/montenegro' },
  { title: 'Hungary for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/hungary' },
  { title: 'Bulgaria for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/bulgaria' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'serbiaFit', header: 'Serbia Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RSD 32,000-45,000/mo', serbiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RSD 38,000-54,000/mo', serbiaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RSD 29,000-42,000/mo', serbiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'AXA Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'RSD 27,000-40,000/mo', serbiaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Serbian RFZO', entryAge: 'No limit', renewal: 'N/A', monthlyFrom: '10.3% income', serbiaFit: 'For Residents' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'RSD 29,000-45,000', annual: 'RSD 348,000-540,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'RSD 40,000-60,000', annual: 'RSD 480,000-720,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'RSD 54,000-82,000', annual: 'RSD 648,000-984,000' },
  { category: 'Serbian Public (RFZO)', monthly: '10.3% income', annual: 'Contribution-based' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'RSD 3,000-8,000/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Serbia 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Serbia. Belgrade vibrancy, affordable living, growing healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Serbia"
  subheadline="Serbia offers vibrant Belgrade, affordable living, improving healthcare, and warm Balkan hospitality—an emerging destination for budget-conscious retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/serbia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Serbia</h2>
  <p>
    Serbia offers excellent value—vibrant capital life in Belgrade, rich history, warm hospitality, and very affordable living. While not EU, Serbia is modernizing rapidly with growing private healthcare sector. The legendary Serbian hospitality makes integration welcoming.
  </p>

  <p>
    Belgrade provides cosmopolitan energy with fortress, rivers, and nightlife famous across Europe. Novi Sad offers calmer university city life and hosts EXIT Festival. Niš has history and even lower costs. The countryside provides rural peace at minimal expense.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; good private options in Belgrade</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Serbian; English in Belgrade; Cyrillic script</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> RSD 90,000-200,000/month (~$850-1,900)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; hot summers, cold winters</li>
      <li><strong>EU Status:</strong> Candidate; not expected soon</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Vibrant, hospitable, historically rich</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Serbia's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Serbia has public healthcare through RFZO (Health Insurance Fund). Quality in public sector is mixed—facilities can be dated, waits long. Private healthcare has grown significantly in Belgrade with modern clinics (Bel Medic, Euromedik, Medigroup) offering good care.
  </p>

  <p>
    Belgrade's private hospitals are adequate for most needs. Outside Belgrade, quality drops. For complex care, Hungary (Budapest) is accessible. Medical tourism is growing—Serbia offers good dental and cosmetic work. International insurance recommended for quality care.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Public vs Private Reality</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Serbian public healthcare is free for residents but crowded and underfunded. Expats typically rely on private clinics in Belgrade—modern facilities, English-speaking staff, reasonable prices. International insurance provides access to private care and evacuation options for complex needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Serbia offers welcoming options for retirees:
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visa-Free Stay</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities get 90 days visa-free. Can exit to neighboring country briefly and return for another 90 days. Some retirees use this pattern for extended informal stays.
  </p>

  <h3>Temporary Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For those demonstrating sufficient income (typically €600+/month) and health insurance. Valid 1 year, renewable. Relatively straightforward process through Ministry of Interior.
  </p>

  <h3>Property Ownership</h3>
  <p>
    Foreigners can own property in Serbia (with reciprocity requirements). Property ownership combined with income proof supports residence application.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Serbia:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence application:</strong> Health insurance required</li>
    <li><strong>RFZO access:</strong> Residents can contribute to public system</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> For quality care in Belgrade clinics</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Consider for complex care (Hungary nearby)</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Serbia</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for residence applications and recommended for quality private care. Belgrade's private clinics are affordable (RSD 3,000-6,000 consultations) for routine needs. Keep international for specialists, complex care, and potential evacuation to Hungary or EU.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Serbia, these providers offer good coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Serbia</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good European network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Balkans pricing</li>
    <li><strong>Hungarian access:</strong> Budapest reachable for advanced care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers that work well for Serbia.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Serbia are among Europe's lowest:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local private care is cheap; high deductible works</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations RSD 3,000-6,000; easy cash</li>
    <li><strong>Balkans coverage:</strong> Plans covering Serbia + Hungary efficiently</li>
    <li><strong>RFZO option:</strong> Can contribute to public system if desired</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Digital Nomad Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,800/month pension + occasional consulting. Loves Belgrade energy.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for visa and coverage. Uses Bel Medic private clinic. US coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~RSD 38,000/month (~$360). Lives excellently in central Belgrade.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension £2,000/month. Seeking value and culture.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for both. Live in Novi Sad (calmer than Belgrade). UK coverage included.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~RSD 95,000/month combined (~£810). Excellent lifestyle on pension.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Hungarian Neighbor, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Hungarian citizen (EU). Moving to Subotica (Serbian-Hungarian border). €1,100/month pension.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz covering both. Uses Serbian private locally. Hungary for complex care (1 hour away).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Allianz ~RSD 32,000/month (~€290). Best of both worlds.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Serbia safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, generally safe. Belgrade is vibrant at night; petty crime exists but violent crime is rare. Football rivalries can create tensions on match days. Political protests occur occasionally. Overall, it's a safe retirement destination with standard urban precautions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the Cyrillic script?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Serbian uses both Cyrillic and Latin scripts—street signs often show both. Official documents are typically Cyrillic. Learning Cyrillic basics is helpful (it's not hard—33 letters, phonetic). In Belgrade's international areas, Latin script is common.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Belgrade's private healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Good and improving. Private clinics (Bel Medic, Euromedik, Medigroup) offer modern facilities, English-speaking staff, and reasonable prices. Adequate for most senior needs. Complex cases may need Budapest (4 hours). Quality drops significantly outside Belgrade.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">When will Serbia join the EU?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Uncertain—negotiations are ongoing but slow. Kosovo issue complicates matters. Don't move expecting imminent EU membership. Serbia has its own character and benefits without EU status. Costs would likely rise with EU membership anyway.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers that work well for Serbia retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Serbian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
